{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_9","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"rtk which icm && rtk icm --help | sed -n '1,120p'\"","aggregated_output":"/home/drdave/.local/bin/icm\nInfinite Context Memory - persistent memory for LLMs\n\nUsage: icm [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>\n\nCommands:\n  store             Store a new memory\n  recall            Search memories\n  list              List memories\n  forget            Forget (delete) a memory by ID, or all memories in a topic\n  update            Update an existing memory in-place\n  health            Show memory health report (staleness, consolidation needs)\n  feedback          Feedback subcommands — record and search prediction corrections\n  transcript        Transcript subcommands — verbatim sessions + messages (session replay)\n  extract-patterns  Detect recurring patterns in a topic and optionally create memoir concepts\n  topics            List all topics\n  stats             Show global statistics\n  extract-pending   Process the async extraction queue (LLM-backed). Reads pending raw tool outputs captured by hooks when `extraction.summarizer.provider != none` and runs the configured LLM CLI to extract facts. Designed to be invoked from a cron, a SessionEnd async fork, or manually\n  decay             Apply temporal decay to memory weights\n  prune             Prune low-weight memories\n  consolidate       Consolidate all memories of a topic into a single summary\n  embed             Generate embeddings for memories that don't have one yet\n  memoir            Memoir commands — permanent knowledge layer\n  init              Configure ICM integration for Claude Code / Claude Desktop\n  doctor            Diagnose ICM integration: check hook binary paths in Claude Code settings\n  uninstall         Reverse `icm init`: remove ICM config from every detected AI tool\n  bench             Run performance benchmark on in-memory store\n  extract           Extract facts from text and store in ICM (rule-based, zero LLM cost)\n  import            Import conversations from external sources (Claude.ai, ChatGPT, Claude Code, Slack, text)\n  recall-context    Output recalled context formatted for prompt injection\n  recall-project    Auto-recall context for the current project (detects from PWD / git remote)\n  wake-up           Print a compact critical-facts pack for LLM system-prompt injection\n  save-project      Auto-save context for the current project (detects from PWD / git remote)\n  learn             Scan a project and save its structure as a Memoir knowledge graph\n  bench-recall      Benchmark memory recall accuracy with and without ICM\n  bench-agent       Benchmark Claude Code efficiency with and without ICM\n  bench-format      Compare token cost of recall payload formats (JSON / TOML / TOON / compact)\n  config            Show current configuration\n  upgrade           Upgrade icm to the latest release (with SHA256 verification)\n  cloud             RTK Cloud commands (login, sync, status)\n  serve             Launch MCP server (stdio transport for Claude Code)\n  hook              Claude Code hook handlers (read JSON from stdin, output hook response)\n  hook-log          Show recent hook telemetry rows (start, end, post, pre, prompt, compact)\n  hook-stats        Aggregate hook telemetry: counts, error rate, and latency percentiles per event\n  dashboard         Launch interactive TUI dashboard\n  help              Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)\n\nOptions:\n      --db <DB>        Path to the SQLite database. Audit #185 medium: `clap`'s `global = true` lets the same flag appear at both the parent and subcommand level (`icm --db A stats --db B`), with the last occurrence winning silently. We collect into a `Vec` so we can detect that case and reject it with a clear error instead of letting the user lose data with the wrong DB\n      --no-embeddings  Disable embeddings (skip model download, use keyword search only)\n  -h, --help           Print help\n  -V, --version        Print version\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
